DPRK , ROK reach agreement on cooperation in light industry and underground resources
chinanews , july 8
North korea and south korea today reached an agreement on cooperation in light industry and underground resources development .
according to the agreement , the ROK will provide the DPRK with raw materials for the production of light industrial products such as garments , and in this regard , the DPRK will grant the ROK mining rights in some domestic mines .
according to a report by the japan broadcasting association , the ROK and the DPRK held business - level consultations in Kaesong in three days on cooperation in light industry and underground resource development , and finally reached an agreement .
according to this agreement , the ROK will provide the DPRK with raw materials for the production of garments , shoes , and soap within this year , with a total value equivalent to 9.8 billion yen .
to this end , the DPRK will grant mining rights to three mines in the country to the ROK .
the south Korean government will ship the first batch of 500 tons of fiber from the western port of Incheon on july 25 .
according to the plan , starting from 28 july , the ROK and the DPRK will jointly investigate mines in the eastern part of the DPRK .
at the end of last month , the south Korean government began a plan to provide 400,000 tons of rice to north korea .
after the DPRK expressed its willingness to actively implement the agreement reached through negotiations among the six countries , including the closure of nuclear facilities , economic cooperation between the DPRK and the ROK has once again become active .
Lanzhou price bureau explains beef noodle price limit : only because the increase is too large
chinanews , Lanzhou , july 10
this afternoon , the Lanzhou city commodity price bureau invited relevant departments to hold a forum on the issue of price limits on beef noodles .
at the press conference , it was learned that the main reason why the city 's commodity price bureau and other departments jointly issued a price cap on paper was that beef noodle prices had risen too much , which was beyond the ordinary residents ' ability to withstand .
according to statistics , the price of beef noodles has risen by as much as 20 percent this time , the shortest and largest increase since the Lanzhou beef noodle price rose for the first time in the early 1980 s .
the government 's action is to take into account the economic capability of ordinary residents in this region . we introduced the price ceiling after a cost survey , said the director of the commodity price bureau of Zhanlanzhou city .
on 26 april , the Lanzhou city commodity price bureau , the industry and commerce bureau , the health bureau , and four other departments jointly imposed a maximum price on beef noodle in the city . once the news was revealed , it aroused strong concern .
it has been learned that the purpose of the forum was to extensively listen to the opinions of various circles and solicit opinions and suggestions for the next step of introducing specific management measures . it was also revealed that Lanzhou will hold a news conference tomorrow .
this will be the second news conference held in Lanzhou city on the beef noodle price increase incident .
Ministry of civil affairs punishes china regional development promotion association : stop activities for three months
chinanews , july 11 - according to information from the website of the ministry of civil affairs , on july 9 , the ministry of civil affairs imposed an administrative penalty of three months ' suspension of the activities of the china regional development promotion association .
the punishment order shows that the china regional development promotion association has committed the following illegal acts : 1 ) collecting dues in excess of the standard ; 2 ) collecting other fees from non - member units using receipts for membership fees .
according to investigations , the membership fee standard of the association is 2,000 yuan per year . from june 2005 to february 2007 , the association issued receipts to more than 20 units . in addition to the 2,000 yuan membership fee collected by one unit member , the other units collected fees ranging from 10,000 yuan to 100,000 yuan , totaling more than 800,000 yuan , including management fees collected from branches and internal organs . this seriously violated relevant laws and regulations .
in accordance with the provisions of article 33 , paragraph 1 ( 8 ) , of the " regulations on the registration and management of social organizations , " the ministry of civil affairs imposed an administrative penalty of three months ' suspension of the association 's activities and sealed the association 's seal and other related articles according to law .
