Wang Yan &apos;s injury improved and he insisted on sitting on the bench and regaining his upper limb strength .
Wang Yan can already sit up on the bench , but not for long , otherwise she will feel dizzy .
Wang Yan , who was injured earlier in the competition , is still recovering from her injuries . among them , her left and right upper limbs have regained their muscle strength compared with those of more than 10 days ago , and she has been promoted to the second level of guinea pig .
on 4 april , when wang Yan was transferred from the ICU ( intensive care unit ) of the Shanghai no. 6 hospital to the special needs ward , her right upper limb strength ranged from 2 to 3 , and her left upper limb strength ranged from 1 .
nearly half a month later , wang Yan 's upper limb muscle strength has further improved .
Dr tan said wang Yan 's right hand had a muscle strength of more than four levels , only one level lower than the normal five levels , and her left hand also had a muscle strength of more than three levels , tan said .
that is to say , in less than half a month , wang Yan 's upper limb muscle strength recovered to the second - level dart .
not long ago , Wang Yan was able to sit in bed for five minutes with the help of a doctor .
the hospital 's rehabilitation experts had originally planned to let wang Yan practice touching the ground under the protection of the rehabilitation bed last weekend .
