Venezuelan president Chavez says he will slash wages for senior civil servants
chinanews , july 23 - Venezuelan president Hugo Chavez delivered a long speech on Venezuela 's internal and foreign policies on july 22 .
he said that the salaries of senior civil servants had been drastically cut .
he added that foreigners coming to Venezuela would face serious consequences if they attacked the Venezuelan government and would be expelled from the country .
Chavez has ordered government officials to closely monitor what foreigners say when they visit Venezuela , and found that anyone who openly criticizes him or the Venezuelan government will be expelled from the country .
he said in a televised speech on the evening of the 22 nd that Venezuela will not tolerate foreigners coming to the house to tell us what to do .
in his speech , he also pointed out that the salaries of senior civil servants will be greatly reduced .
he said that the highest salary of Venezuelan civil servants could not exceed 7,000 us dollars per month .
it is reported that in Venezuela , the monthly income of some poor people is 250 us dollars .
in latin american countries , it has become a common practice to cut civil servants ' wages , and this has won the support of the broad masses of the people .
leaders of peru , Bolivia , and other countries all cut their salaries themselves .
Chavez also said that Cuban leader Castro reminded him to pay attention to assassinations directed by the us side .
