the F1 spy case hearing ended yesterday . McLaren got away with it .
last night , beijing time , a special hearing convened by the FIA motor sports council on the Ferrari technology espionage case ended in Paris . the McLaren motorcade , which was summoned , escaped : the council decided not to punish McLaren for the time being .
the official website of the international automobile federation issued a statement after the hearing , saying : " at present , there is not enough evidence to prove that the secret Ferrari information is being used improperly in the FIA formula one world championships and therefore no penalty will be imposed . "
however , the Ferrari technological espionage case has not come to an end .
in the decision , the auto sports council also said : " we reserve the right to ask the McLaren team to return to the auto sports council for a hearing if it finds out in the future that Ferrari 's relevant information will be used to harm the championship . at that time , they may face the penalty of being disqualified from the 2007 season or even the 2008 season . "
former McLaren chief designer Mike Koglan , who has now been suspended from his post , was found to be in possession of nearly 800 pages of Ferrari technical documents , including the design , driving force , construction , inspection , testing , development , and operation of the Ferrari 2007 car .
McLaren insisted that no one else in the team knew about the information before Coagland was suspended and that there was no Ferrari element in McLaren 's car this season .
