in order to further promote the healthy development of our country 's maritime industry and expand our country 's fleet of ships , and in view of the relevant problems arising from the registration and flying of foreign flags by a considerable number of ships engaged in international navigation in china , the ministry of communications recently issued a " circular on the implementation of the tax exemption registration policy for special cases involving chinese - funded international shipping vessels , " clarifying the conditions and application procedures for enjoying the tax exemption policy for special cases . starting from 1 july this year , ships that meet the requirements will be exempted from customs duties and import link value - added tax if they apply for import declaration within two years .
Shanghai , Tianjin and Dalian may be selected as the port of origin for ship registration procedures .
