don &apos;t let the vendors bother you in public places .
going out for a trip is aimed at relaxing , refreshing , being at ease , and maximizing the enjoyment of the fruits of natural scenery and social civilization .
however , when traveling in the country , many people encounter this kind of trouble and are chased and intercepted by vendors and intermediaries in public places .
no matter if it is a car or a train that gets on or off the train , it always encounters small vendors and some unlicensed intermediaries .
it is either selling eggs , peanuts , and scones , or newspapers and magazines , or many unlicensed intermediaries introduce food and beverage accommodation , and even peddle fake certificates and fake invoices .
if you do n't accept it , he can chase you for several hundred meters , and there is a strong tendency to become benevolent if you do n't succeed .
in some scenic spots , many tourists feel the same way .
before entering the gate , some people came to peddle tourist souvenirs and small handicrafts and so on .
after entering the house , the situation became even more so , and no matter how good the taste was , it was completely uninteresting to stir it up .
it has been reported in the media that many foreign tourists to xian have been full of praise for the scenic spots and monuments in xian , but they are incomprehensible for allowing a large number of small business hawkers to peddle everywhere .
public places , including stations and scenic spots , are originally places for travel and leisure . we should pay attention to civilization and order , peace and harmony , and provide a comfortable and relaxed environment for tourists .
the free entry and exit of vendors has disturbed the minds of tourists , objectively disrupted the public order of these public places , created visual pollution and environmental pollution , and also provided lawless elements with the conditions and opportunities to stir up trouble .
what is important is that these public places are windows to the building of the local spiritual civilization . a glimpse shows the whole leopard . what is damaged is not only an image problem , but also an impact on the local economic development .
just think , if you want to become a big and strong tourism industry , but you use such a messy tourism environment to welcome guests from the south to the north , who will still want to come , and who dares to come ?
how does your economy benefit from tourism ?
with the arrival of the peak tourism season , it should be said that it is an urgent task to create a civilized tourism environment for tourists from all parts of the world .
public places are not markets , and the operations of small traders and hawkers should be standardized , those operating without licenses should be resolutely abolished , and illegal activities should be resolutely cracked down upon .
only by maintaining a civilized and orderly environment can visitors be happy to come , enjoy themselves , and come back again .
in a word , do n't let vendors bother you in public places .
