rapid shrinkage of Alpine glaciers due to climate change
Xinhua news agency , geneva , july 29 , by reporter jun liu
a long - term follow - up study by glaciers experts at the Swiss academy of sciences found that between 1850 and 2005 , more than 1,800 glaciers in Switzerland were shrinking at an average annual rate of 3% .
heat waves in 2003 alone caused the Alpine glaciers to melt by 1.8% .
experts believe that by 2100 , if global temperatures rise by 3 degrees celsius , glaciers will shrink by 80% , and if they rise by 5 degrees celsius , glaciers will melt completely .
the Alec glacier , the longest glacier in europe , has been listed on the unesco world natural heritage list , but has shrunk by 100 meters between 2005 and 2006 , making it imperative to protect the natural environment .
the picture shows Alec glacier up to 23 kilometers long .
photo by Liu Jun
