the number of reports of adverse reactions caused by the diabetes drug Avandia has soared
the number of reports of adverse reactions such as heart attacks caused by the anti - diabetic drug Avandia has risen sharply in the united states recently , us media reported Tuesday .
the us food and drug administration issued a safety warning in may this year advising diabetics to be cautious with Avandia because scientists published a research report in the may 21 issue of the new England journal of medicine , saying that this best - selling drug would greatly increase the incidence of heart disease and mortality among patients .
Avandia &apos;s safety is therefore closely watched by doctors and patients .
statistics show that within about a month after the safety warning was issued , the us drug administration received 357 reports of adverse reactions caused by vendia , 38 of which were death reports .
in january and february this year , the FDA received only 50 and 73 reports of adverse reactions respectively .
these adverse reactions ranged from blistering to sudden cardiac death .
however , drug experts from the us drug administration believe that it is too early to conclude that Avandia is unsafe .
the FDA will hold a hearing on the safety of Avandia on july 30 .
Avandia was introduced in 1999 as an insulin sensitizer for type ii diabetes mellitus .
about 6 million diabetics around the world have taken or are taking Avandia .
Avandia 's producer , britain 's GlaxoSmithKline , has always believed that Avandia is safe and that the advantages to patients outweigh the disadvantages .
