13 pilots resign , china eastern Wuhan company claims more than 100 million yuan in counterclaims
Xinhua news agency , Wuhan , july 11 ,
thirteen pilots resigned , and the china eastern airlines Wuhan limited liability company issued a huge compensation bill amounting to 105 million us dollars . this is the largest labor dispute bill so far in Hubei province .
the Hubei provincial labor dispute arbitration commission is currently hearing the case .
in may this year , 13 pilots of the Wuhan company of the china eastern airlines successively submitted their resignations , which were rejected by the company .
subsequently , in early june , the pilot successively filed an application for labor arbitration with the Hubei provincial labor dispute arbitration commission , requesting an adjudication to terminate his labor relations with the Wuhan company of china eastern airlines .
after receiving the notice of response , the Wuhan company of china eastern airlines filed a counterclaim , demanding that 13 pilots pay them losses ranging from more than 6 million yuan to more than 10 million yuan , totalling 105 million yuan , resulting from the cancellation of the labor contract in violation of the labor contract agreement .
it has been learned that the pilots signed an indefinite labor contract with china eastern airlines . apart from the suspension or cancellation conditions stipulated in the labor contract , the validity of the labor contract will continue until the pilot 's legal retirement age .
the Hubei provincial labor dispute arbitration commission will hear the case both as an appeal and as a counterclaim , and the hearing is expected to be concluded before august 8 .
