in one month 's time , hurriedly transferring funds and money is enough time .
if i were a corrupt official , i would definitely think so , and i would never go to your place to voluntarily declare .
corrupt officials always behave like this when they are thankful : Haha , thank you ...
the common people are really perplexed . what on earth is wrong with this anti - corruption campaign ? why is it so difficult to act swiftly and decisively ?
what role will such anti - corruption play ?
in short , the central discipline inspection commission , i 'm worried about the effectiveness of your anti - corruption plan .
the bottom line of my peace of mind is not to privatize the land .
Tseng tsung - du , a Buddhist nun , sent a short message to tseng tseng tseng - tseng tseng - tseng - tseng on 2007 - 07 - 02 10 Tseng 34 Tseng - 39
the bottom line of my peace of mind is not to privatize the land .
I think i 'm a person who doesn't get angry easily , at least my own feelings are like this .
it has always been reasonable and peaceful to speak at the forum , and it is rare to lose one 's reason and make nonsense .
I have always maintained a high degree of confidence in and ardent expectations of the party central committee . no matter how incompatible the reform measures are with my concept , i can accept them as one of the characteristics of guinea pig .
but once land is privatized ( or privatized in disguise ) , all of this will lose its basis .
it is better to lose thousands of troops than to lose an inch of land . land and resources are the biggest social resources .
the working people and the land and resources are the foundation of a country .
as long as the nature of land and resources remains unchanged , the nature of this country will be very difficult to change . once the nature of land and resources changes , then basically everything will change .
I am not a communist , but i clearly remember that i once vowed to love the motherland and the people , to study hard , to train well , and to be ready : to contribute my strength to the communist cause !
he studied hard , worked hard , endured hardships first , enjoyed later , and struggled for the communist cause !
like me , the people who swore this oath and sang loudly that we were successors to socialism , if they were not shameless enough , should remember their oath .
if you have already betrayed your own oath , please stand up frankly and walk away from the bangladesh , and do not deceive the masses with this signboard while pondering how to sell this signboard at a good price .
of course , may all this worry be superfluous , and may I always be rational and calm .
remember , we are the successors to socialism .
what if there is no shift to take over ?
the feelings of one generation and two eras
some time ago , it was suggested ; does a 30 - year - old have hair ?
later changed to 20 .
in fact , people in this age group have never experienced Mao Zedong 's era at all , and it is not known whether the person who raised this question was suffering from brain watering or congenital brain dementia .
in cities , the people who have the most say in Mao Zedong 's era should be those who experienced that era , those who suffered from what era , that is to say , those who were born between 1950 and 1960 .
after they were born , their parents took part in sports and did not give their children relative love .
when they needed nutrition , they caught up with three years of natural disasters and suffered from hunger .
when they began to go to school , they encountered the great cultural revolution and abandoned their studies for several years .
some of them have even completed their studies for the rest of their lives . before they have completed their studies , they are forced to give up their studies , answer the call of the party , go to the countryside , and support the border areas .
after working , they believe that the working class is the most honorable and voluntarily chooses the dirtiest and most tiring jobs .
I was honored for a while and lost my life .
when they got married , they married late and had only one child and they started again .
they should be paid a higher salary , enterprises talk about diplomas , but they cannot grow without diplomas .
they have worked hard to raise their children to complete their basic education , their children have been admitted to university , and they have caught up with the double frost of reforming the educational system , the double frost of reforming state - owned enterprises , and tuition fees have risen , and they have been laid off .
as they grew older , they began to get sick . unfortunately , they caught up with the reform of the medical system . as a result , their sick bodies could not afford medical treatment because they could not afford it .
it can be seen that the injustice of the whole society has been relentlessly brought down on their generation .
however , among these people , there were few who opposed Mao Zedong and attacked Mao Zedong .
why is that ?
they are not the slaves of Mao Zedong , they are flesh and blood , and they truly live in our social group of people , and they face the social phenomena of the two eras squarely in the history of their personal experience from going to the mountains and the countryside to being laid off and unemployed .
although they have a lot of dissatisfaction , even hatred , with Mao Zedong 's desolation of studies , inadequate food and clothing , and some unhealthy phenomena in society , they still think Mao Zedong 's era is better in terms of national spirit , ethics , and social atmosphere .
some netizens ' parents are of this generation , and you can chat with them .
author : 3 ft 3 2005 - 6 - 23 19 min 16
the Cancer Banana Bazaar and the Bazaar Bazaar Bazaar Injection
I remember the news the year before last that Hainan watermelons had been injected with chemicals by syringes , resulting in a large number of Hainan watermelons rotting in the fields and a large number of farmers losing their lives .
CCTV later made a follow - up report , but the result confirmed that there was no such thing at all .
this report was bizarre from the beginning , because injecting a large watermelon with a syringe is not only of no practical significance , it is also impossible in terms of workload .
last year , the memory was even clearer . according to media reports , banana trees in Hainan suffered from a disease similar to human cancer , and the diseased banana trees were bound to die .
as a result , it was misunderstood by many people that bananas would cause cancer . the result was the same . the banana prices in Hainan fell sharply , causing banana farmers to cry their eyes out and cry bitterly .
the reason why these two reports have produced a sensation is because they have directly touched the most sensitive root of people 's nerves , that is , the issue of food safety .
if the media say that certain foods will endanger health , then they will certainly spread the word from person to person . as far as the targets involved are concerned , people generally adopt an attitude of preferring to believe that they exist rather than to believe that they do not exist . for a person , it is not a great thing to eat a few Hainan watermelons and bananas less . however , for those who produce and sell these products , the impact will be great .
not long ago , there was another explosion in beijing about food safety , that is , because of the increase in pork prices , some people actually used carton boxes to make stuffing to produce stuffed buns , that is , carton stuffed buns .
I was also deeply shocked when i heard this , and felt that this little dealer was so capable of studying that he was able to come up with such a trick , and subsequently spread the news widely , warning his family and friends not to buy steamed stuffed bun any more on the street .
however , there was a sudden news report yesterday that the carton steamed stuffed buns report was a fake news story , and the whole thing was fabricated by one person . so while he was relieved , he also wondered what happened to the media today .
what i have learned from reliable sources is that the temporary staff of the " transparency " column of the beijing television station 's life channel accused a certain person of bringing his own meat fillings , flour , and cartons purchased from the market , and instructed wei and others to soak the cartons in water and mix them with meat fillings to make steamed buns .
Zi filmed the production process with his own home DV machine , and then edited it and broadcast it by deception .
at present , public security organs have already detained criminal suspects in accordance with the law and will seriously deal with them in accordance with the law .
after the steamed stuffed bun incident , the government promptly organized relevant departments to conduct an investigation and carried out an all - round and thorough inspection of the beijing breakfast market to ensure the safety of the common people 's dining tables .
after the incident was confirmed , the beijing television station publicly apologized to the society , profoundly learned a lesson , seriously investigated and punished those responsible , and will further strengthen management , plug loopholes , and resolutely put an end to false and untrue news reports .
however , although the carton stuffed buns are completely out of the question , it is still unknown when people will dare to go to the stall to buy stuffed buns again with confidence .
this incident also reflects the importance attached by the government to the food safety issue and the swift action taken by the government . to a certain extent , it also shows that the dining tables of the ordinary people in beijing are still relatively safe . the bun incident caused a false alarm , and it also serves as a wake - up call for everyone !
who should be responsible for education ?
recently , listening to friends in China talking about a school experience , I can not help but feel .
it happened at Southwest Weiyu Middle School , a private middle school in Shanghai .
the school has decided to assign the best teachers to three classes that have signed up from junior middle school to senior high school , while a few young teachers who have no senior three teaching experience and have not performed well in the past will be allowed to bring several other classes that have entered or not signed up for admission to the school from other schools .
the reason is : the students who signed the contract agreed to give up the examination of other high schools at that time , so the school should guarantee them the best teachers according to the agreement .
as for the students in several other classes , the school 's attitude is to give young teachers the opportunity to exercise .
this makes me sigh with emotion : who is responsible for education ?
I remember many years ago , when i was attending a key high school , my classmates were dissatisfied with the teaching level of a math teacher , no matter how high or high it was , they collectively signed a request for the school to replace the teacher .
later , the school really changed our teachers , because the school promised us that we would treat every student equally and be responsible to every student .
ten years ago , he came to the united states to study as a graduate student .
one summer when i took the next semester 's course , i found that all the elective courses in the department were theoretical and some applied courses were not arranged at all .
I went to talk to the dean and told him that I thought there was something wrong with the curriculum .
the dean admitted that the lack of applied courses was due to the shortage of teaching staff , which would be available in a year or two .
I remember saying to him at that time : this is your problem , not mine .
I came all the way from Shanghai to your school because I was attracted by your introduction .
if you can &apos;t afford to run these courses , don &apos;t put them on the introduction , otherwise it &apos;s a false advertisement and irresponsible to me and my family .
the dean listened to me and thought , I &apos;ll see what I can do .
it may be too late because all the courses are already scheduled for registration online .
after three weeks , the dean talked to me to the effect that his job was to be responsible to every student , including me .
he listened to my advice and did his best to add two applied electives , which i hope i can understand .
after this incident , I took several classes from the dean of the department .
he never prejudiced against me because I gave him advice , and gave me A &apos;s fairly in every subject .
on the eve of graduation , i heard from his secretary that he did his best for every student , but not every student was grateful to him .
speaking as a representative of honorary students at the graduation ceremony , i told the dean : each of us is grateful to him from the bottom of our hearts for what he has done for us , because he has done his best to be responsible for each of us .
I feel like I made the right choice to go to school here .
speaking of this , i see a faint tear in the eyes of the dean of the department . if one day every chinese educational worker and the entire educational system can be held accountable to every student , i think the day will not be far off when china will really take off .
Central NYMen 4 s Volleyball Tournament
last Sunday we played in the men 's four - man volleyball match in central new york for six and a half hours , and our team finally won the championship .
the competition is actually a training competition organized in preparation for a volleyball match at the New York State Summer Games .
the coach broke up four men 's teams ( the high school team , the college team , the team over 35 , and the team over 45 ) in central new york and reorganized them into a four - man team , each equipped with a two - pass .
the rules of the game are very interesting . you can only attack in the back row , you can not drop the ball within the three - meter line , you can only block the ball with two passes and one person without changing positions .
so basically it is to test the strength of the strong attack and the defensive judgment card position .
our team had a 2 - meter receiver , and the offense was both strong and high . he handled more than 60 percent of the offense and score for the whole game . a 1 - meter - 85 two - pass was blocked by a single player .
a one - meter - 90 secondary attack , due to being in the back row , made a lot of offensive mistakes .
in addition , i , the 1.75 meter main attack , sometimes sneak attack , the success rate is quite good , the main receiver is the other side 's slant spike .
there were seven teams , first in the round robin , and after our team won one game , the referee repeatedly ordered us to step on the line in response to the attack , which greatly affected our morale and caused us to lose three games in a row .
however , after losing the game , everyone 's psychology calmed down and cooperation reached stability in the three games , so they began to win in succession .
at the end of the round - robin , our team won three games and lost three games .
in addition to the first team , the second - to - seventh team will play the knockout match .
our team is psychologically and tactically stable , that is , playing hard and eating hard , leading the team all the way to the semifinals .
the semi - final opponent attacked the strong and defended the weak and hit my arm black and blue , but once i picked up a heavy clasp , i was twice as happy as if i had succeeded in clasping a ball myself .
I don &apos;t know what the final score was .
the opponents in the final were in a balance of attack and defense , and our side had a lot of serve breakers , leading all the way .
at the last 21 : 24 , our side held the match point , and the other side even asked me to take off with two shots . at 23 : 24 , our team 's receiver came up to me and said , " it 's okay , it 's just two balls . "
the next ball came at me again , luckily i caught it well , passed it back to the receiver , and hit a heavy button to settle the battle .
tell me more about morality .
a lot has been said about morality for the scattered free individual .
I have nothing more to say in this regard .
now what I want to say is about the group .
sometimes we run into situations where we need to work together .
on these occasions , it is necessary for a collective to have certain morals .
we often find some good morals in groups that have been successful .
this is not accidental .
because as far as these causes or activities are concerned , it is necessary to overcome certain immediate difficulties , unite as one , and get rid of those factors based on belief , i think it is also those good morals that have played a role that cannot be ignored .
at the very least , it is very difficult for a group of people with very low moral standards to work together to achieve great success , and this can be predicted with great confidence .
this may be because the wisdom to see long - term interests through a rational long - term perspective is a necessary quality for a collective success .
in fact , collectives often acquire IDENTITY in various ways , such as logo , jargon , belief , and so on , as well as morality .
only in the morning brandy , in the evening brandy , the road to life can orchid everywhere .
( discussion ) how many times have you been truly happy to have lived to this day ?
my high school friend finally got a visa and was able to leave at the end of august to study for graduate school in the west coast of the united states .
today , when several students gathered together , they were really happy for her and finally got what they wanted .
seeing her so happy , i really envy her .
when i think about growing up , i was only so happy when i got into high school , i never thought that i would be able to get into one of the best schools in the city , and then , naturally , i would go to college and work , and in the meantime i would never be so happy again .
the university entrance examination was not the one i had hoped for before , so i was not very happy to talk about it .
during my college years , my only sustenance was to go to the north after graduation and meet my GG , which i had been in love with for two years .
however , fate played tricks on me . a month before i graduated , he broke up with me , and all my previous fantasies vanished .
after that , i went back to work in the north , and today , i have been working for almost two years , earning money from a medium - sized car , but i have never been so happy again .
today , when i chatted with my friend , i could very well feel her happiness , trembling with fear , and after a year of painstaking preparation , i finally went abroad smoothly to start a new life . the feeling that my dream has come true is really very happy .
I did not plan to continue studying and did not like life abroad , because after working abroad for half a year , i found that life abroad was not suitable for me .
see the happiness of good friends , I can not help but think , my pursuit ?
what can make me so happy again ?
maybe i want to find someone who really likes me and is willing to go with me for the rest of my life .
I think at that time , i would cry excitedly , just as my good friend told me that when she passed the embassy interview and got the customs clearance , she could not help crying , and after a year of hard work and worry , she finally got something in return .
and me ?
emotionally , i trembled again and again and worked with my heart . when will i be able to fulfill my wish and cry happily ?
perhaps it is not promising , I always do not worry about their own career , just feelings ?
when will my feelings come to an end ?
I am always sad about this problem .
Ladies and gentlemen , what about you ?
how many times have you lived to be truly happy ?
