Nanjing subway driver should receive psychological debugging as soon as possible
key Word : psychological debugging
according to Xinhua news agency reports , on the evening of 3 july , a death occurred on the Nanjing subway .
according to the reporter 's description , tan Ching - ting , 22 , a young subway driver , had a nightmare scene . when the reporter saw him yesterday , he did not seem to have recovered from his fear . he sat down in his chair , straightened out , and his eyes looked a little dizzy .
obviously , this young driver 's spirit has been greatly impacted , and it is urgent to carry out psychological debugging , otherwise he will be harmed for life .
I wonder if everyone remembers that the rescuer who rescued a young girl from an abandoned oil well in Texas in the united states more than 10 years ago finally chose to end his painful life by committing suicide after enduring mental torture .
at that time , although he had been subjected to simple psychological debugging , because more attention had been paid to the little girl who had been rescued , those who needed psychological debugging had been neglected , and in the end tragedy had not been averted .
similarly , in the smuggling incident in the Dover strait a few years ago , the first british policeman to open a container was said to have been stunned on the spot .
it took the british side more than two months of psychological debugging to get him back to normal .
when a person is stimulated by a disaster , his or her psychology will be greatly harmed . at this time , it is very difficult for him or her to recover completely on his or her own strength alone , and psychological scars are often left behind .
since such scars are difficult for outsiders to discover and there is no way to do so , many of the people involved will suffer for the rest of their lives .
however , people in our country do not pay enough attention to psychological trauma . in particular , the families or departments in charge of the victims often suddenly think of it after they have lost the best recovery period . it is already too late .
nowadays , with the diversification of the media , we often hear of appalling incidents in which many young women have been harmed and many young children have witnessed the cruel harm inflicted on their parents .
after the juveniles were rescued , they were rarely heard to have received psychological treatment and were more likely to be comforted by relatives .
although the victim can feel safe , the former injury has become a scar that can never be cured and will always be awakened , affecting the life of the person concerned .
fortunately , the driver 's leader promptly reassured him and relieved his mental pressure .
after all , the driver is not responsible for the accident , and the driver also took measures when he discovered the situation . he has already done what he should have done , but he has not stopped the tragedy from happening .
it is believed that even if it is not the driver involved , everyone present will be shocked by the accident that occurred at the scene .
however , other people are not responsible for the suicide , and although they were shocked , they will gradually fade away with the development of time .
the driver was less fortunate and had to remember , probably for the rest of his life .
if he can extricate himself from this scene , he will be lucky , and if he cannot extricate himself , he will often be tormented by this kind of scare .
the concept of modern health is more comprehensive than in the past , and mental health has begun to attract people 's attention .
what is regrettable is that the human mental condition is very frustrating . especially in cities , people 's mental health is very unsatisfactory . most people have more or less hidden spiritual dangers , and some people have encountered problems that have not aroused enough attention .
think about the lesson of the previous stage of the tan yang Lijuan incident , some irresponsible media used a patient suffering from mental problems as the object of hype , causing a very bad social impact .
we should avoid such incidents in the future , otherwise our society will really become a morbid society .
