however , sometimes it seems that life cannot be completely calculated according to the results , that life is used to slowly feel , and that peace , stability , fulfillment , and joy are also a kind of harvest , although this kind of harvest can sometimes not be measured by social evaluation standards .
everyone needs to recognize social value and self - worth . if we cannot have both , what will happen to us ?
Marxism teaches us to give priority to social values and advocates that individuals should make contributions to society . however , in reality , a healthy and healthy society should also fully respect the wishes and value choices of individuals and create conditions for the realization of individual values .
it suddenly occurred to me that the Marxist principles were really very effective .
this is indeed the truth , but when it comes to real life , it is hard to avoid being puzzled at times .
even if the realization of self - worth does not obstruct social value , will every real individual of us be satisfied with the realization of true self - worth without regard to social evaluation ?
or is our sense of self - worth contentment detached from social evaluation ?
it seems very difficult .
therefore , while each of us strives to be an ordinary person , it is unavoidable to pursue excellence and transcendence , and if we waste our lives , we will always blame ourselves .
this is probably the social aspect of people .
