two trees .
two trees , one is me , the other is my brother - in - law .
we kept each other cool and cared for each other .
my generation have many children , but I only have a sister , no brother and brother , so the presence of brother-in-law is very important .
we were all born poor children and had to take part in a great deal of housework at a very young age . although i always tried to pretend to be a big man and wanted to work like an expert , i never got my father 's permission .
I &apos;ve had sleepwalking since I was a kid , but it &apos;s not that serious , but when it comes to housework , distractions are inevitable .
for example , my father asked me to muddy the chimney of the old house , and i quickly climbed onto the roof to operate .
the chimney was wiped , but when it rained , the house was dewy because I crushed the tile .
for example , my father asked me to change the light bulb , that old incandescent light bulb .
when I climbed onto the stool , the light bulb in my hand fell off and broke on the concrete floor .
there are countless examples of this , so when my brother - in - law entered the room , he took it for granted that he contracted the chores and did them beautifully , at no labor cost .
I could not bear to hide in a corner and read those casual books that looked like bricks .
later , we grew up to be two trees , two big enough to support a family building .
however , his father inevitably dwarfed down , and sitting in his wheelchair , he became an obscure bush in the shade .
unexpectedly , the 50 - year - old brother - in - law suddenly became seriously ill , and the seemingly lush and luxuriant trees unexpectedly approached the fearful death .
on that dizzying summer day , outside the operating room of Beijing Union Hospital , the doctor downplayed the words : there is no surgical value .
he has two months to live at most .
at that moment i felt as if i had been suddenly hit by stray bullets , and my soul had suddenly shrunk out of its shell , and all the fools were there .
I began to sleepwalk again and saw the old courtyard of my home and the busy figure of my young brother @-@ in @-@ law in the courtyard .
it was my sister 's shrill cry that awakened me . I hurried to hug my sister , who was sitting on the hospital porch , and we hugged each other in tears .
the bright sun suddenly disappeared , and my eyes darkened in front of me .
after returning to our city from beijing , my brother - in - law soon learned of his illness . after he and my sister hugged each other and cried bitterly , their feelings turned to relief .
my brother @-@ in @-@ law began to arrange things in an orderly way , such as telling his son : take care of your grandmother for me . when she dies , she will be reunited with your grandfather and how to open the tomb .
visit your grandfather often and buy him some practical things in time for the New Year &apos;s Day .
for example , he told my sister : after i left , you should visit your sister often , she must be very lonely all by herself .
I took as much time as I could to see him , but he looked ashamed of me .
we are often speechless , like two plants that cannot talk even though they are alive .
these are two adult trees . the experience of wind and rain has enabled us to calmly face the hardships . what else do we need to explain to me ?
doesn &apos;t seem necessary .
because you know in your heart : after you leave , your sister , your sister , your children , and everyone else , you can only rely on this tree of mine to support you alone .
who told me to be a man ?
it is a man , whether you like it or not , you must not hesitate to straighten your spine and lift responsibilities .
the only regret is : why did your tree wither so early , you should have a lush old age ah ?
the day you left was the first day of the lunar new year .
that is , when the chinese people all over the world greeted the spring festival with joy , you left alone .
perhaps , in another time and space , another bud of life is born ?
